text: 150px Jiang Youfeng also written as Jiang Yufeng, Tsjiang Tsjioeng Feng or Tsjing Yu Fen (born April 1949) is a Chinese former long track speed skater, who was active in the 1970s. After having for 5 years no Chinese speed skaters at the World Allround Speed Skating Championships for Women, Jiang Youfeng represented China at the 1972 World Allround Speed Skating Championships for women in Heerenveen together with skater Tien Cailian. It was also evident from the a Dutch newspaper report, that their participation was remarkable. At these championships there was also a Chinese Chargé d'affaires, La Mao, to see the women's compete. Jiang Youfeng finished 30th overall. The year later she also competed at the 1973 World Allround Championships in Strömsund, finishing 26th overall.
